import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['age'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    plt.bar('Average Height', data['height'].mean())
    plt.axhline(y=data['height'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Height: {data['height'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Height')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the average height of individuals in the dataset?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=800, background_color='white', min_font_size=10).generate_from_frequencies(name_counts)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8), facecolor=None)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.tight_layout(pad=0)
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['height_bins'] = pd.cut(data['height'], bins=5)
    age_by_height = data.groupby(['height_bins'])['age'].apply(list).reset_index(name='age_list')
    age_by_height['age_list'] = age_by_height['age_list'].apply(lambda x: np.array(x))
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for i, row in age_by_height.iterrows():
        ax.hist(row['age_list'], bins=10, alpha=0.5, label=row['height_bins'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the age distribution for individuals of different heights in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
